# Why this architecture is interesting

This project isn't just about implementing hardware. It demonstrates **system-level engineering**:

* Modular hardware blocks with well-defined interfaces.
* A realistic memory hierarchy centered on scratchpad SRAM and DMA.
* Performance instrumentation from day one.
* Verification infrastructure designed alongside the RTL.
* A clean path for AI agents to analyze regressions, performance, and debug data.

That combination is uncommon in personal projects and aligns closely with the kinds of engineering practices used in modern accelerator teams.

